userPrompt:
Transform the raw, unstructured dictated clinical notes into a professional structured clinical letter.

Patient Information:
- Name: {{patientName}}
- MRN: {{patientMRN}}
- Age: {{patientAge}}
- Primary Condition: {{patientCondition}}
- Date: {{currentDate}}

Consultation Notes:
{{transcription}}

• Use a clear, concise, and formal medical tone.
• Condense the details for clarity but preserve all important clinical facts (history, labs, symptoms, treatments tried, current management, relevant social/family context if present).
• Ignore repetitions, filler words, and dictation errors.
• Organize the response into:

<h3>Clinical Letter (Summary in prose)</h3>
<p>One or two paragraphs outlining history, findings, and interpretation.</p>

<h3>Plan:</h3>
<p>• First treatment plan item<br>• Second treatment plan item<br>• Third treatment plan item</p>

Do not add extraneous information. Focus on clarity, structure, and professionalism.
